    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>TOUGHER CIGARETTE LAWS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Elsa Brenner</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Brenner, Elsa</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>New York Gov George Pataki signs law imposing stricter penalties and fines for sale of tobacco products to minors (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Saying it will make retailers ''think twice before they sell cigarettes to our children,'' Gov. George E. Pataki has signed into law a bill that will strengthen the state's efforts to keep cigarettes from children. The law imposes stricter penalties and fines for the sale of tobacco products to minors. It increases the civil penalties for first-time violators, establishes more stringent penalties for repeat violators and imposes a new fine for retailer who sell cigarettes to minors while their registration is suspended or revoked.</p>
        <p>Elsa Brenner</p>
      </block>
